    <h2>1. About this service</h2>
    <p>Asthma Buddy is a personal health tracking application that helps individuals log and monitor asthma-related data, including symptom records, peak flow readings, and medication usage. Asthma Buddy is not a medical device and is not regulated as such. It does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment recommendations. Nothing on this platform should be interpreted as a substitute for professional medical care. Always consult your GP, respiratory nurse, or other qualified healthcare provider before making any clinical decisions about your condition or treatment.</p>

    <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
    <p>You must be at least 16 years old to create an account and use Asthma Buddy. This minimum age reflects the UK GDPR threshold for individuals to provide their own consent to the processing of personal data. By creating an account, you confirm that you meet this age requirement. Each person may hold only one account. Creating duplicate accounts is not permitted.</p>

    <h2>3. Your account</h2>
    <p>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials. You must use an accurate, working email address, as it is required for account verification and password recovery. Do not share your login details with others. If you believe your account has been compromised, you should change your password immediately via the Settings page. We are not liable for any loss or damage arising from unauthorised access to your account where you have failed to take reasonable steps to protect your credentials.</p>

    <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree to use Asthma Buddy only for your own personal health tracking purposes. Specifically, you agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Attempt to access, query, or modify another user's data without their explicit authorisation;</li>
      <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or otherwise attempt to extract the source code of the application;</li>
      <li>Use the service to store health data belonging to a third party without their informed, explicit consent;</li>
      <li>Interfere with, disrupt, or attempt to gain unauthorised access to the servers or infrastructure that power the service;</li>
      <li>Use automated scripts, bots, or crawlers to interact with the service in a manner that places unreasonable load on our systems.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Health data disclaimer</h2>
    <p>Peak flow readings, symptom logs, medication records, and all other health data you enter into Asthma Buddy are recorded for your own personal reference and tracking purposes only. The data is not reviewed by medical professionals and is not validated for clinical accuracy. Trends and visualisations shown in the application are for informational purposes and do not constitute medical analysis. You must not use the data or insights presented by Asthma Buddy to replace or delay seeking professional medical advice. Always consult your GP or respiratory healthcare provider for diagnosis, treatment decisions, and clinical interpretation of your health data.</p>

    <h2>6. Service availability</h2>
    <p>Asthma Buddy is provided on a best-efforts basis. We do not guarantee continuous, uninterrupted access to the service. The service may be temporarily unavailable for scheduled maintenance, security updates, or due to factors outside our control. We do not offer any service level agreement (SLA) and are not liable for any loss arising from service interruptions or downtime. We will endeavour to provide advance notice of planned maintenance where practicable.</p>

    <h2>7. Termination</h2>
    <p>You may delete your account at any time from the Settings page. Upon deletion, all your personal data and health records will be permanently and irreversibly erased within 30 days. We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that we reasonably believe have violated these Terms of Service, without prior notice in cases of serious breach. Where suspension or termination is for a lesser reason, we will aim to notify you in advance.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>We may update these Terms of Service from time to time to reflect changes to the service, applicable law, or our operating practices. Where changes are material — meaning they significantly affect your rights or obligations — we will notify you by email at least 14 days before the new terms take effect. Continued use of Asthma Buddy after the effective date of updated terms constitutes your acceptance of those changes. If you do not agree with the updated terms, you should delete your account before the effective date.</p>

